==Demographics==
As of the 2020 census there were 154 people, 79 housing units, and 98 families in the CDP. There were 116 [[White Americans|White]] people, 0 [[African Americans]], 16 [[Native Americans in the United States|Native Americans]], 2 [[Asian Americans|Asians]], 2 from some other race, and 18 from two or more races. There were 14 people with [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] origin.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile?g=160XX00US4126400 |access-date=2023-05-25 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The median age in Fort Hill was 57.9 years old. 43.4% of the population were between the ages of 75 and 84. 30.1% of the population were veterans.<ref name=":0" />

The median household income was $16,914, but 0.0% of the population were in poverty.<ref name=":0" />

